Building TensorFlow:
===================
This uses the dependencies built using EasyBuild.
Check https://gitlab.version.fz-juelich.de/nassyr1/juawei-easyconfigs for more info 
Or contact: Salem El sayed <s.elsayed@fz-juelich.de>
            Stepan Nassyr <s.nassyr@fz-juelich.de>


Instructions:
------------------
- Set the correct $mod_path in environment.sh
  ex. for visnode-0X:
  mod_path=/scratch

- Source environment.sh:
    $ source environment.sh
  This loads all modules and sets all required environment variables

- Extract the tensorflow tar directory
    $ tar -xvf v1.15.2.tar.gz
  (source https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/archive/v1.15.2.tar.gz)

- Apply the swig patch TensorFlow-1.15.2_swig-env.patch.
  This can also be done manually by editing tensorflow-1.15.2/tensorflow/tensorflow.bzl
    
- Configure tensorflow
    $ cd tensorflow-1.15.2/
    $ ./configure
 
- Set the build path in build_line.sh
    ex. 
    build_path=/path/to/my/tensorflow/BUILD

- Run the build script from within the tensorflow direcotry
    $ cd tensorflow-1.15.2/
    $ ../build_line.sh

- while ( Not building correctly ) 
    Assess life's worthiness
    DEAL WITH ERRORS!!!!

